0P0001247P.L.manager_bio:
Over 12 years experience in the design of financial products and services;
Graduated with distinction from Wits University in 1994;

1995 - 1997: lectured in applied mathematics in the Department of Computational and Applied Mathematics at Wits University;

1997 - 1999: joined Standard Corporate & Merchant Bank as an interest rate derivatives trader;

2000 - 2003: worked for Peregrine Securities as a research/sales trader focused on hedge fund trading strategies;

2003: founded Legae Capital, the first black owned and woman-managed fund of hedge funds in South Africa. Under Fatima, Legae Capital became one of SA's leading hedge fund multi-managers;

2006: awarded the Financial Services Pioneer Award by ABSIP (Association for Black Securities and Investment Professionals), previously given to Tito Mboweni and Vuyani Ngalwana;

2006: voted one of SA's top 20 black fund manager executives by the Financial Mail; In 2006 the portfolio of hedge funds managed by Fatima and her team at the time won the Top performing Fund of Hedge Fund award from Hedge Fund Intelligence.

2007: founded 27four Investment Managers, South Africa's first black owned and women run institutional multi-manager.
